	<LINE>Maxton, superintendent ; Miss M.Morton, librarian.</LINE>
	<LINE>The object of the institution is to afi"ord facilities</LINE>
	<LINE>to working men for social intercourse, mutual im-</LINE>
	<LINE>provement, instruction, and rational recreation. It</LINE>
	<LINE>is open daily from 9 a.m. to 10 p.m. The library</LINE>
	<LINE>contains 2000 volumes, including a number of re-</LINE>
	<LINE>cently issued works. The reading room is supplied</LINE>
	<LINE>with all the leading newspapers and magazines.</LINE>
	<LINE>The large halls are allotted for games, including</LINE>
	<LINE>billiards, bagatelle, summer ice, draughts, and chess.</LINE>
	<LINE>Annual subscription, including library, 5s. ; half-</LINE>
	<LINE>yearly subscription, 2s. 6d. ; monthly ticket, 6d. ;</LINE>
	<LINE>do., including library, 8d. ; visitors. Id.</LINE>
